<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.usatoday.com/usatonline/20030211/4854954s.htm">Official comments*</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> on the change in the terrorism threat level, from &quot;yellow&quot; to &quot;orange&quot;, indicate that the FBI believes that WMD will be involved in the next Al Qaida terrorist operation; an operation that appears imminent if it is not broken up first. This could be biological, chemical or radiological. The latter seems most probable to me, at least if the attack is in the United States, since this requires the least amount of smuggled material if a mass casualty event is planned, as seems almost certain. A radiological weapon also has the best potential for generating general panic and disruption with a minimum of effort. A few curies worth of contamination anywhere on the North American continent will send every panic-stricken media conformist who develops a wart or a rash to the emergency room for &quot;symptoms of radiation poisoning&quot;, generating chaos in facilities that are not notably well-ordered at the best of times. <br>
