emselves but how governments might use the threat of terrorism to further erode our rights.  I don't like it that the US government and various states are seeking to increase their police powers in the name of Homeland Security.  Don't get me wrong, I'd far rather the Republicans be in office than the Democrats, but I think both parties have lost the essence of why the constitution seeks to limit government power.  You can quit a company that treats you badly but you can't escape being under the thumb of a tyrannical and self-serving goverment.  In any case I think we should hurry up and finish off Iraq before the summer heat hits.  There's no alternative now but war.    <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nuclaeon>Nuclaeon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>NERVA Spaceplane Pilot</span><br>  Posts: 120<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/11/03 4:42:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sunday morning</span><hr size=1> The only thing that will make it stop is if the fuel behind the fire is gone.  In part we need to stop consuming so much oil.  I believe much US dependence has gotten itself into this mess.  Although that is not to justify the acts of terrorists, it does help cause the problem.  If we shift away from that and actually try and help the affected people, the terrorists recruiting power is drastically decreased.  It's kind of hard to fight the same culture that is building you schools and hospitals, and providing you with training. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#484848><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub97.ezboard.com/bnuclearspace.showUserPublicProfile?gid=atomicconspiracy>Atomic Conspiracy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br>  Posts: 184<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(2/11/03 6:19:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub97.ezboard.com/fnuclearspacefrm8.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=377.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Sunday morning</span><hr size=1> It is essentially impossible to reduce terrorist recruiting with protection money. They only need a handful of people, a few hundred or a few thousand from a population of billions. Anyone with resources and an agenda can find that many. There are millions of Hindus who hate Christianity and the United States and who would like to have billions more in aid from us. In our support for Pakistan, they even have a pretext analogous to the Islamo-fascist hatred of our support for Israel. <br>
